    <bioghist>Sergeant in Co. G, 6th Michigan Cavalry during the Civil War from Shiawassee County, Michigan.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Correspondence describing his wartime activities, 1862-1864, including letters written from Camp Kellogg, Grand Rapids, Michigan, and later as prisoner-of-war from Andersonville Prison; also, prison diary, 1863-1864, written during Civil War at Libby, Belle Isle, and Andersonville prisons; and miscellaneous Kay family papers, 1873-1895, including letters of Mary Ann Kay written from Lansing, and Shiawassee County, Michigan.</scopecontent>
